206 - Reverse Linked List
Problem

Given the head of a singly linked list, reverse the list and return the new head.

Intuition

To reverse a linked list, change the direction of each link.

Use three pointers:

prev → Previous node
curr → Current node
next → Store next node before changing links
Algorithm

Initialize:

prev = null
curr = head
While curr != null:
Store next node.
Reverse current node's link.
Move prev and curr one step forward.
Return prev as the new head.
Code
class Solution {
    public ListNode reverseList(ListNode head) {

        ListNode prev = null;
        ListNode curr = head;

        while (curr != null) {
            ListNode next = curr.next;

            curr.next = prev;

            prev = curr;
            curr = next;
        }

        return prev;
    }
}
Dry Run
Input:
1 -> 2 -> 3 -> 4 -> 5

Iteration 1:
1 -> null
prev = 1
curr = 2

Iteration 2:
2 -> 1 -> null
prev = 2
curr = 3

Iteration 3:
3 -> 2 -> 1 -> null
prev = 3
curr = 4

Iteration 4:
4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 1 -> null
prev = 4
curr = 5

Iteration 5:
5 -> 4 -> 3 -> 2 -> 1 -> null
prev = 5
curr = null
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)
Key Learning

The core reversal pattern is:

next = curr.next;
curr.next = prev;
prev = curr;
curr = next;

